U.S. September Kansas City Fed Financial Stress Index

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-10-11T18:56:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/u-s-september-kansas-city-fed-financial-stress-index-table-.html
 A measure of stress in the U.S.
financial system, based on 11 financial market variables, rose in Sept.,
according to the  Federal Reserve Bank of Kansas City .  A positive value of the KCFSI indicates that financial stress
is above the long-run average, while a negative value signifies
that financial stress is below the long-run average.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Tanzi in  Washington  at   atanzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  